<subSubSection pageId="85" pageNumber="86" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="85.[151,1436,1261,1610]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,319,1477,1502]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Species of average size, colouration contrasted, face yellow with 3 black spots, very similar in colouration and external morphology to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Otte, 2007 a: 351 -" authorityYear="2007" box="[634,796,1514,1537]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Cardiodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="empagatao">
<emphasis box="[634,796,1514,1537]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">C. empagatao</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, to which it differs by brown Sc vein (yellow in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Otte, 2007 a: 351 -" authorityYear="2007" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Cardiodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="empagatao">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">C. empagatao</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), female venation yellow with dark brown cells and male genitalia with three levels in lateral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
